# Mobile Client Environment Variables

# For local development on simulator/emulator:
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8081
EXPO_PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_URL=http://localhost:8080

# For testing on physical device (replace with your computer's IP):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8081
# EXPO_PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8080

# To find your computer's IP address:
# macOS: ifconfig | grep "inet " | grep -v 127.0.0.1
# Linux: ip addr show | grep "inet "
# Windows: ipconfig

# IMPORTANT: When using a physical device, you must also add the redirect URI 
# to Keycloak's client configuration. The format is typically:
# exp://YOUR_IP:8082
#
# Add this via the Keycloak Admin Console:
# 1. Go to http://localhost:8080/admin
# 2. Select realm "reportmaxxing"
# 3. Go to Clients -> mobile-app
# 4. Add your redirect URI to "Valid redirect URIs"
